Obviously not.

1004
01:52:36,224 --> 01:52:38,658
I have to do something!
What?!

1005
01:52:38,864 --> 01:52:41,662
I read something about it in biology!

1006
01:52:42,504 --> 01:52:46,179
"Devil's Snare, Devil's Snare...
to get free...

1007
01:52:46,384 --> 01:52:50,582
you light a candle, of course!
Of course you do! It hates sunlight!

1008
01:52:50,824 --> 01:52:52,780
Lumus Solem.

1009
01:53:00,544 --> 01:53:03,012
Ron are you okay?
Yeah, I'm fine.

1010
01:53:05,624 --> 01:53:07,979
Luckily, we did not panic.

1011
01:53:08,704 --> 01:53:12,060
Good thing Hermione listened to the lessons.

1012
01:53:13,624 --> 01:53:15,057
What is it?

1013
01:53:15,264 --> 01:53:18,813
I don't know... it sounds like wings.

1014
01:53:31,424 --> 01:53:34,734
That's strange. I have never seen such birds.

1015
01:53:34,944 --> 01:53:38,414
They are not birds.
They are keys.

1016
01:53:38,624 --> 01:53:41,934
And one of them probably fits the door there

1017
01:53:45,264 --> 01:53:49,701
What is the point of this?
I don't know what it is.

1018
01:53:55,344 --> 01:53:57,300
Strange...

1019
01:53:57,704 --> 01:53:59,899
Alohomora!

1020
01:54:02,744 --> 01:54:04,894
It was worth a try.

1021
01:54:05,104 --> 01:54:08,221
What are we doing?
There must be 1000 keys up there!

1022
01:54:08,424 --> 01:54:12,178
It's probably an old-fashioned rusty one.

1023
01:54:12,384 --> 01:54:15,660
There it is! The one with the broken wing!

1024
01:54:19,104 --> 01:54:21,334
Is something wrong Harry?

1025
01:54:22,184 --> 01:54:23,617
It is too easy.

1026
01:54:23,824 --> 01:54:28,375
Come on, Harry!
If Snape can catch one, so can you!

1027
01:54:28,584 --> 01:54:31,974
You the youngest searcher of this century!

1028
01:54:48,144 --> 01:54:51,022
This makes it slightly more difficult.

1029
01:55:11,424 --> 01:55:13,255
Catch the key!

1030
01:55:17,504 --> 01:55:19,335
Hurry up!

1031
01:55:50,504 --> 01:55:54,975
I do not like this
Not in the least

1032
01:55:55,184 --> 01:55:58,221
Where are we? In a cemetery.

1033
01:55:58,584 --> 01:56:01,098
This is not a cemetery.

1034
01:56:08,304 --> 01:56:11,102
It is a chessboard!

1035
01:56:22,584 --> 01:56:24,415
There's the door!

1036
01:56:35,984 --> 01:56:37,417
What do we do now?

1037
01:56:37,784 --> 01:56:41,743
Of course it is!
Let's play our way across the room!

1038
01:56:42,304 --> 01:56:45,899
Harry, you take the runner's place.

1039
01:56:46,224 --> 01:56:50,263
Hermione, you will be the tower
closest to the lady.

1040
01:56:50,504 --> 01:56:54,383
And me, I'm a runner!

1041
01:57:01,264 --> 01:57:02,902
What happens next?

1042
01:57:03,664 --> 01:57:06,542
White always starts first.

1043
01:57:06,744 --> 01:57:08,541
and then...

1044
01:57:10,224 --> 01:57:11,418
we play.

1045
01:57:21,584 --> 01:57:26,419
Ron, do you think it will be the same

1046
01:57:26,664 --> 01:57:30,054
...like in real wizard chess?

1047
01:57:30,424 --> 01:57:33,257
You there! D-5!

1048
01:57:47,264 --> 01:57:48,777
Yes, Hermione...

1049
01:57:48,984 --> 01:57:53,853
I think it will be
exactly like wizard chess!

1050
01:57:59,544 --> 01:58:01,933
Runners, to E-4!

1051
01:58:05,424 --> 01:58:07,619
Farmer, to C-3!

1052
01:58:50,424 --> 01:58:54,258
Wait a minute
Listen, Harry.

1053
01:58:54,504 --> 01:58:59,020
When I make my move
the Queen will take me.

1054
01:58:59,624 --> 01:59:01,854
Then you are free to put the king in check!

1055
01:59:02,064 --> 01:59:04,658
No! Ron! Ron, no!
What's happening?!

1056
01:59:05,264 --> 01:59:09,735
He is going to sacrifice himself!
You can't! There must be another way!

1057
01:59:09,944 --> 01:59:13,539
Don't you want to stop Snape from getting the Stone?

1058
01:59:13,744 --> 01:59:17,180
Harry, it is you who must continue!

1059
01:59:17,664 --> 01:59:20,303
Not me, not Hermione, but you!

1060
01:59:30,144 --> 01:59:32,942
Runner to H-3!

1061
01:59:53,024 --> 01:59:54,935
Chess.

1062
02:00:22,904 --> 02:00:24,622
Ron!

1063
02:00:24,824 --> 02:00:30,376
No! Don't move!
Don't forget that we are still playing.

1064
02:00:44,824 --> 02:00:46,052
Checkmate.

1065
02:01:05,184 --> 02:01:07,573
Take care of Ron. Then go to the owls

1066
02:01:07,784 --> 02:01:11,493
and send word to Dumbledore.
Ron's right.

1067
02:01:11,704 --> 02:01:13,501
I have to keep going.

1068
02:01:13,984 --> 02:01:19,661
Don't worry Harry
You are a great wizard.

1069
02:01:19,864 --> 02:01:22,253
Not as good as you.

1070
02:01:23,064 --> 02:01:27,694
Me? Books and wisdom
There are more important things

1071
02:01:28,864 --> 02:01:34,257
Friendship and courage.
Be careful now Harry

1072
02:02:10,784 --> 02:02:12,376
You?

1073
02:02:13,144 --> 02:02:16,819
No, it is impossible! Snape he

1074
02:02:17,024 --> 02:02:19,936
He seems to be that type, doesn't he?

1075
02:02:20,144 --> 02:02:23,136
Because who would suspect

1076
02:02:23,344 --> 02:02:27,098
S-stackars, s-stuttering
Professor Quirrel?

1077
02:02:27,304 --> 02:02:32,458
But when we played the Quidditch match,
Snape tried to kill me!

1078
02:02:32,664 --> 02:02:35,337
No, my boy. I tried to kill you!

1079
02:02:35,824 --> 02:02:39,817
If Snape's cape hadn't caught on fire,
and I lost my eye contact

1080
02:02:40,024 --> 02:02:42,140
I would have succeeded!

1081
02:02:42,344 --> 02:02:45,222
Even if Snape was muttering counterspells!

1082
02:02:45,424 --> 02:02:47,540
Snape tried to SAVE me?

1083
02:02:47,744 --> 02:02:52,864
I knew you were a danger to me.
Especially after All Hallows' Eve.

1084
02:02:53,064 --> 02:02:57,137
So it was you who let the troll in?
Excellent Potter. Yes.

1085
02:02:57,344 --> 02:03:00,222
However, Snape was not fooled.

1086
02:03:00,784 --> 02:03:05,539
When everyone went to the basement
he was on the 3rd floor to stop me.

1087
02:03:06,424 --> 02:03:09,780
He didn't trust me anymore after that.

1088
02:03:10,744 --> 02:03:15,772
He rarely left me alone.
But he doesn't understand.

1089
02:03:15,984 --> 02:03:19,863
I am never alone. Never.

1090
02:03:20,064 --> 02:03:23,977
Well, what does this mirror do?

1091
02:03:25,504 --> 02:03:27,540
I see what I want

1092
02:03:28,064 --> 02:03:32,296
I see myself holding the stone.
But how do I get it?

1093
02:03:32,504 --> 02:03:34,574
"Use the boy"

1094
02:03:35,344 --> 02:03:39,098
Come here Potter! NOW!

1095
02:03:50,704 --> 02:03:54,538
Tell me, what do you see?

1096
02:04:18,664 --> 02:04:20,973
What is it? What do you see?!

1097
02:04:21,184 --> 02:04:26,133
I shake hands with Dumbledore.
I have won the dormitory cup.

1098
02:04:26,344 --> 02:04:27,823
"He is lying"

1099
02:04:28,304 --> 02:04:31,853
TELL THE TRUTH! WHAT DO YOU SEE?!

1100
02:04:32,064 --> 02:04:36,262
"Let me talk to him"
Master, you are not strong enough!

1101
02:04:36,504 --> 02:04:40,338
"I have enough strength... for this"

1102
02:04:57,784 --> 02:05:00,537
Harry Potter...

1103
02:05:00,744 --> 02:05:02,974
...we meet again.

1104
02:05:03,184 --> 02:05:04,537
We meet again.

1105
02:05:04,744 --> 02:05:08,532
Yes, it is. Do you see what has become of me?

1106
02:05:08,784 --> 02:05:12,220
Do you see what I have to do to survive?

1107
02:05:12,424 --> 02:05:16,383
Sharing my body with someone else...
Like a parasite.

1108
02:05:17,024 --> 02:05:20,221
Unicorn blood can strengthen me.

1109
02:05:20,424 --> 02:05:23,939
But not enough to create a body of their own.

1110
02:05:24,144 --> 02:05:27,534
But there is something that can.

1111
02:05:27,744 --> 02:05:33,182
Something that is just enough. It's in your pocket.

1112
02:05:33,544 --> 02:05:35,023
Stop him!

1113
02:05:39,864 --> 02:05:42,503
Don't be a fool!

1114
02:05:42,984 --> 02:05:45,976
Why face certain death

1115
02:05:46,184 --> 02:05:49,654
when you can unite with me
and continue living?

1116
02:05:49,864 --> 02:05:50,899
Never!!!

1117
02:05:52,824 --> 02:05:57,420
Courage. Your parents had it too.

1118
02:05:58,144 --> 02:06:01,295
Tell me, Harry...

1119
02:06:01,544 --> 02:06:05,253
Would you like to see your mother and father again?

1120
02:06:05,504 --> 02:06:07,495
Together...

1121
02:06:07,704 --> 02:06:10,138
we can get them back.

1122
02:06:10,544 --> 02:06:15,060
All I ask for is little things in return.

1123
02:06:21,504 --> 02:06:24,496
That's right Harry

1124
02:06:25,344 --> 02:06:29,053
There is no good and evil.

1125
02:06:29,264 --> 02:06:32,142
There is only power.

1126
02:06:32,344 --> 02:06:36,303
And those who are too weak to seek it out

1127
02:06:36,944 --> 02:06:41,779
Together we can do incredible things

1128
02:06:42,184 --> 02:06:44,334
only you give me the stone!

1129
02:06:46,864 --> 02:06:47,979
You liar!

1130
02:06:48,184 --> 02:06:50,220
Kill him!

1131
02:07:12,784 --> 02:07:17,904
What kind of magic was that?
Idiot! Take the Stone!

1132
02:08:58,864 --> 02:09:01,253
Good afternoon, Harry

1133
02:09:03,304 --> 02:09:07,616
Gifts from your admirers.
Admirers?

1134
02:09:07,824 --> 02:09:13,581
What happened between you and
Professor Quirrel is an absolute secret.

1135
02:09:13,784 --> 02:09:18,380
So... of course... the whole school knows about it.

1136
02:09:20,624 --> 02:09:24,094
I see Ron has saved you the trouble
with

1137
02:09:24,304 --> 02:09:27,023
to open your chocolate frogs.

1138
02:09:27,224 --> 02:09:30,102
Is he okay?
and what about Hermione?

1139
02:09:30,304 --> 02:09:34,980
They are both fine.

1140
02:09:35,544 --> 02:09:38,217
What happened to the stone?
Calm down my boy

1141
02:09:38,544 --> 02:09:41,263
The stone has been destroyed.

1142
02:09:41,504 --> 02:09:45,543
My friend Nicolas and I had a little chat

1143
02:09:45,744 --> 02:09:49,532
and agreed that it was for the best.

1144
02:09:49,744 --> 02:09:53,419
But won't Flamel die then?

1145
02:09:55,384 --> 02:10:00,663
He has enough elixir of life in stock
to get his affairs in order.

1146
02:10:00,864 --> 02:10:03,936
And then, well... he will die.

1147
02:10:04,144 --> 02:10:06,499
How could I get the stone?

1148
02:10:06,704 --> 02:10:09,138
First it was in the mirror
And then in my pocket.

1149
02:10:09,344 --> 02:10:13,257
You see, only a person...

1150
02:10:13,544 --> 02:10:17,298
Only the one who wanted to find the stone.

1151
02:10:17,544 --> 02:10:21,901
But not using it
could get it.

1152
02:10:22,824 --> 02:10:26,180
It is one of my better ideas.

1153
02:10:26,384 --> 02:10:31,219
Between you and me... that's saying something.

1154
02:10:32,624 --> 02:10:37,618
Now that the stone is gone,
Voldemort will never come back?

1155
02:10:37,824 --> 02:10:40,054
I am afraid that...

1156
02:10:41,424 --> 02:10:45,303
there are possibilities that he can return.
in which he can return.

1157
02:10:45,984 --> 02:10:48,452
Harry, do you know why...

1158
02:10:48,664 --> 02:10:52,498
Do you know why Professor Quirrel
couldn't stand you touching him?

1159
02:10:52,704 --> 02:10:57,141
It was because of your mother.
She sacrificed her life for you.

1160
02:10:57,664 --> 02:11:00,736
That kind of action leaves a mark.

1161
02:11:00,944 --> 02:11:04,573
No, this mark cannot be seen.

1162
02:11:04,784 --> 02:11:09,494
It's under your skin.
What is it, then?

1163
02:11:10,304 --> 02:11:13,899
Love Harry. Love Harry

1164
02:11:21,624 --> 02:11:25,583
Oh, Bertie's multi-flavor beans!

1165
02:11:25,784 --> 02:11:30,255
I had the misfortune in my youth,
to get a vomit-flavored one.

1166
02:11:30,504 --> 02:11:33,655
Since then I have not really liked them.

1167
02:11:33,864 --> 02:11:37,095
Well, I should be able to feel safe.

1168
02:11:37,304 --> 02:11:39,579
with a good caramel taste.

1169
02:11:43,504 --> 02:11:44,983
Unfortunately...

1170
02:11:45,664 --> 02:11:47,700
Earwax!

1171
02:12:02,304 --> 02:12:05,341
Okay, Ron?
Okay, uh... How about you?

1172
02:12:06,424 --> 02:12:09,018
Hermione?

1173
02:12:09,664 --> 02:12:11,416
Never had it better.

1174
02:12:26,584 --> 02:12:28,939
Another year has passed!

1175
02:12:29,664 --> 02:12:34,021
My understanding is that
students should be rewarded.

1176
02:12:34,224 --> 02:12:36,738
The position is as follows:

1177
02:12:36,944 --> 02:12:42,496
In fourth place...
Gryffindor with 312 points.

1178
02:12:44,384 --> 02:12:49,822
In third place...
Hufflepuff with 352 points.

1179
02:12:54,904 --> 02:12:56,622
In second place...

1180
02:12:56,824 --> 02:13:01,420
Ravenclaw with 426 points.

1181
02:13:06,864 --> 02:13:08,502
And in first place

1182
02:13:08,824 --> 02:13:14,023
with 472 points, Slytherin.

1183
02:13:19,384 --> 02:13:21,500
Nice one, mate.

1184
02:13:25,184 --> 02:13:29,097
Yes, yes! Bravo Slytherin!

1185
02:13:29,344 --> 02:13:33,462
Anyway...New events must be taken into
be taken into account

1186
02:13:33,664 --> 02:13:38,419
I have some "last minute" points to share.

1187
02:13:39,024 --> 02:13:44,303
Ms. Hermione Granger...
For her use of cold logic...

1188
02:13:44,504 --> 02:13:47,177
when others were in great danger

1189
02:13:47,864 --> 02:13:50,014
50 points.

1190
02:13:50,904 --> 02:13:52,132
Well done.

1191
02:13:59,544 --> 02:14:05,335
Second... to Ronald Weasley...
For the best chess game...

1192
02:14:05,824 --> 02:14:10,852
ever played at Hogwarts...
50 points.

1193
02:14:15,304 --> 02:14:17,260
Thirdly.

1194
02:14:17,784 --> 02:14:20,537
...to Mr. Harry Potter...

1195
02:14:20,744 --> 02:14:24,862
For his outstanding courage and his great presence of mind

1196
02:14:25,424 --> 02:14:30,100
I award on behalf of Gryffindor 60 points.

1197
02:14:38,064 --> 02:14:39,895
We are equal with Slytherin

1198
02:14:40,104 --> 02:14:45,861
And finally...It takes great courage to
to resist your enemies.

1199
02:14:46,064 --> 02:14:49,773
but even more so to resist
against their friends.

1200
02:14:49,984 --> 02:14:52,817
I give it 10 points...

1201
02:14:53,024 --> 02:14:56,096
to Neville Longbottom.

1202
02:15:08,904 --> 02:15:12,180
If my calculations are correct

1203
02:15:12,384 --> 02:15:16,741
we need a small change in the decorations.

1204
02:15:21,584 --> 02:15:24,815
Gryffindor wins the dormitory trophy!

1205
02:16:01,304 --> 02:16:04,501
Come on, come on! Come on, hurry up! You'll be late.

1206
02:16:04,704 --> 02:16:08,822
The train is leaving soon! Come on, let's go.
Come on, hurry up.

1207
02:16:14,024 --> 02:16:17,175
Just a moment.

1208
02:16:23,184 --> 02:16:26,779
You weren't going to leave without saying goodbye, were you?

1209
02:16:29,864 --> 02:16:31,616
This one is for you.

1210
02:16:47,704 --> 02:16:49,740
Thank you Hagrid.

1211
02:16:55,344 --> 02:16:59,576
There you go, off you go. And by the way Harry...

1212
02:16:59,984 --> 02:17:04,262
Would your cousin Dudley.
That dork... give you trouble

1213
02:17:04,504 --> 02:17:07,064
you can always.....

1214
02:17:07,264 --> 02:17:10,017
threaten him with a pair of ears
to match his pigtail.

1215
02:17:10,224 --> 02:17:15,093
We're not allowed to practice magic outside Hogwarts.
You know that.

1216
02:17:15,544 --> 02:17:19,696
I know that...but your cousin doesn't,
does he?

1217
02:17:24,984 --> 02:17:27,976
Doesn't it feel strange to go home?

1218
02:17:28,184 --> 02:17:30,175
I am not going home.

1219
02:17:30,384 --> 02:17:33,015
Not really.

1220
02:17:32,216 --> 02:17:40,216
www.Undertexter.se
